---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

---

<BaseLayout
  title="Oiva"
  bareTitle
  description="Oiva is an open-source, self-hosted service for AI-assisted incident investigation."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="eyebrow">Open-source incident investigation</p>
      <h1>Oiva</h1>
      <p>
        Oiva turns production alerts into evidence-backed investigation reports by combining observability data, codebase context, and team delivery workflows.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button button-primary" href="/case-study/overview/">Read the case study</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="/getting-started/overview/">Get started</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <section class="flow-panel" aria-label="Oiva workflow overview">
      <div>
        <span>1</span>
        <strong>Alert received</strong>
        <p>Honeycomb-style alert payload starts the workflow.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>2</span>
        <strong>Investigation launched</strong>
        <p>Agents gather telemetry and codebase evidence.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>3</span>
        <strong>Report delivered</strong>
        <p>Slack updates and final findings reach the team.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="overview-grid" aria-label="Oiva capabilities">
    <article>
      <h2>Investigates alerts</h2>
      <p>Placeholder copy for how Oiva enriches noisy production alerts with practical context.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>Connects signals</h2>
      <p>Placeholder copy for combining observability data with repository and codebase information.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>Delivers results</h2>
      <p>Placeholder copy for live Slack updates, final reports, and reviewable investigation output.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>Runs self-hosted</h2>
      <p>Placeholder copy for the Mastra, OpenTelemetry, Postgres, Terraform, and AWS architecture.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="next-step">
    <p class="eyebrow">Next step</p>
    <h2>Start with the structure, then go deeper.</h2>
    <p>This first site pass uses placeholder copy while preserving the planned routes, navigation, and content architecture.</p>
    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button button-primary" href="/case-study/overview/">Case Study</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href="/getting-started/overview/">Getting Started</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: 3rem;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(20rem, 0.9fr);
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: var(--container-wide);
    min-height: calc(100vh - 4.25rem);
    padding: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem) var(--space-page) 3rem;
  }

  .hero-content {
    align-self: center;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(4rem, 14vw, 9rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 0.9;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero-content > p:not(.eyebrow) {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .flow-panel {
    align-self: center;
    background: var(--color-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .flow-panel div {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .flow-panel span {
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-accent-strong);
    border-radius: 999px;
    color: var(--color-background);
    display: inline-flex;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    height: 1.75rem;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    width: 1.75rem;
  }

  .flow-panel strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .flow-panel p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
  }

  .overview-grid,
  .next-step {
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: var(--container-wide);
    padding: var(--space-section) var(--space-page) 0;
  }

  .overview-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .overview-grid article {
    background: var(--color-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .overview-grid h2,
  .next-step h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .overview-grid p,
  .next-step p:not(.eyebrow) {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .next-step {
    max-width: 760px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .next-step .button-row {
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .hero {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      min-height: auto;
    }

    .overview-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .overview-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
